arvelously entertaining narrative. How do stars live and die? What are the prospects of intelligent life elsewhere in the universe? How did the universe begin? Why is it expanding and accelerating in the process? Is our universe alone or part of an infinite multiverse? Exploring these and many other questions, this pocket-friendly book is your passport into the wonders of our evolving cosmos.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAstrophysicsvPopular works. 0aAstrophysics-Popular works. 0aCosmologyvPopular works. 0aCosmology-Popular works. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Astrophysics.2bisacsh1 aGott, J. Richard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGott, J. Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrauss, Michael A., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aStrauss, Michael A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTyson, Neil deGrasse, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 adeGrasse Tyson, Neil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2021 Englishz978311075416208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2021z9783110753936oZDB-23-DPC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073912140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691223612zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691223612423Coveruhttps://www.degru